7) The definition of a cost frontier is c(y,w) = minx {wTx: x ∈ L(y)}. A DMU has two outputs and tree inputs with these values y = {23.619; 11.942} and x = {19.139; 10.854; 8.644} and the input prices w = {7.336; 9.602; 11.687}. The optimal input quantities that minimizes cost are x* = {18.313; 8.639; 7.544} and the input oriented technical efficiency is 0.898.
7.i) Calculate the cost efficiency of this observation and (ii) decompose it between technical and allocative efficiency;
7.ii) Provide a graphical representation of the decomposition.
